    public class House.Cuboid.Rectangle
extends java.lang.Object

    • Field Detail

      • wallType

        private char wallType
        This tells the type of the wall. The wall type is 'w' if the wall is constructed along the width of the house. The wall type is 'l' if the wall is constructed along the length of the house. The wall type is 'f' or 'c' if the wall represents the floor or the ceiling respectively. However, you do not need to worry much about it. It is made sure that in the constructor, a correct value is passed

      • wallLength

        private int wallLength
        This is the length of the wall which will be assigned depending upon the wallstate. If the wallType is 'w', then the wallLength is the roomWidth. If the wallType is 'l' then the wallLength is the roomLength. Otherwise the wallLength is the roomLength itself.

      • wallWidth

        private int wallWidth
        The wallWidth is always the roomHeight except in the cases when wallType is 'f' or 'c' in which case the wallWidth is the roomWidth itself.

      • wallState

        private char wallState
        This denotes the wallState of the wall.

      • Rectangle

        public Rectangle​(char wallType,
                 boolean isRaining)
        Constructor for objects of class Rectangle
        Parameters:
        wallType - Initialises the wallType of the Rectangle by the given value.
        isRaining - isRaining is a boolean variable which is used to initialise the wallSTate of the Wall. If it is raining, i.e. if isRaining is true, then wallState must be assigned 'b' (bad) otherwise, it must be assigned 'g' (good) So, a wall is said to be good if it is in good state and bad if it is in bad state
